      ## A brief history

      * 1882: Frank Miller first describes the one-time pad
      * 1917: Gilbert Vernam reinvents and patents in 1919
      * Early 1920's: German cryptographers Kunze, Schauffler, and
        Langlotz make a similar discovery
      * WWII: Forces on both sides put related systems to use
      * 1945: Claude Shannon reports proof that one-time pads are
        unbreakable, publishes his work in 1949

